    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>to a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> to the pan with your <strong>ground cumin</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir it all together</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and and cook for a further 2-3 min or until thickened - this is your <strong>Tex-Mex style spiced tomato sauce</strong></p>",
